<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-21-1122 </DOCNO><TEXT>We discuss a possible new mechanism leading to stimulated ionic transportprocesses in electron-irradiated glasses. By invoking percolation throughstructurally relaxed units following defect recombination we can givea unified picture of various experimental results. Peculiarities in thetransport properties are shown to give some insight into the nature ofthe irradiation-induced defects in glasses.</TEXT></DOC>